                <h4>Cultural Heritage Management</h4>
                <p>
                    Cultural heritage management involves the strategic planning, preservation, conservation, and promotion of various aspects of
                    cultural heritage within a given society or community. It encompasses a range of activities aimed at safeguarding and sustaining
                    cultural heritage for present and future generations.
                    The objectives of cultural heritage management typically revolve around: Preservation and Conservation, Promotion and Education,
                    Sustainable Development, Community Engagement and Participation.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="courses-col">
