    <section class="courses">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="courses-col">
                <h4>What is Cultural Heritage</h4>
                <p>
                    Cultural Heritage Course delves into the rich and diverse tapestry of human history, traditions, art, architecture, 
                    and practices that define various societies. It explores the significance and preservation of tangible and intangible 
                    cultural elements, imparting insights into the importance of safeguarding and promoting heritage for future generations. 
                    Through interdisciplinary studies, these courses cover topics such as heritage management, preservation techniques, community 
                    engagement, and the role of cultural heritage in sustainable development. Participants learn to appreciate, analyze, 
                    and contribute to the conservation and dissemination of cultural legacy, fostering a deeper understanding and respect for 
                    global heritage.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="courses-col">
                <iframe width="500" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/CbnXgvCOuIg?si=aoIa4Wbelthq5yKh" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>
